    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drawings made by using an implement comprising thin, sharpened rods of silver, usually in a holder, on a support of paper, parchment, or wood treated with a prepared wash or gesso. Ivory may also be used as a support. The silver lines oxidize quickly, making the drawing more distinct, but still delicate and fine.</Note_Text>
